sentences: Maria Rita Brondi (5 July 1889 – 1 July 1941) was an Italian guitarist, lutenist, singer, composer, and music historian.
She was mentioned as a peer of Italian musicians Elisabetta Oddone (1878-1972) and Geni Sadero (also known as Eugenia Scarpa, 1886-1961), though both of them outlived her.
She wrote a book on the history of the guitar, titled Il liuto e la chitarra (1926), which was published in several editions through the twentieth century.
